Package net.hudup.core.data

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AutoCloseable
    This interface establishes the rule that all classes which implements AutoCloseable has a mechanism of auto-closing.
    Dataset
    Interface of recommendation database which is called conventionally dataset.
    ExternalQuery
    Alg is the most abstract interface for all algorithms.
    Fetcher<E>
    Fetcher is the interface for iterating each item of an associated collection.
    Profiles
    This interface represents a collection of profiles.
    Provider
    Dataset only provides read-only operations via "get" and "fetch" methods.
    ProviderAssoc
    Any class that implements this interface is called provider associator which assists the provider specified by interface Provider to performs read-write operations.
    ProviderAssoc.CsvReader
    Interface for CSV reader.
    ProviderAssoc.CsvWriter
    Interface for CSV writer.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDataset
    This abstract class implements partially Dataset interface.
    Attribute
    As a convention this class is called attribute.
    AttributeList
    This class represents a list of attribute, called attribute list, as a convention.
    AttributeValue
    This class represents the pair of attribute and value.
    BooleanWrapper
    This class is a wrapper of boolean value and so its main internal variable BooleanWrapper.value is a boolean value.
    CData
    CData represents a fragment of XML code that is not processed by browser, called CDATA.
    Condition
    Condition is the special profile which is used in condition clause where in SQL statement for processing database, for example.
    DataConfig
    Configuration utility class stores configuration properties.
    DataDriver
    DataDriver is the final class representing specific data types such as system file or database.
    DataDriverList
    This class contains a list of DataDriver and provides utility method on processing such list such as adding new data driver and finding a data driver.
    DatasetAssoc  
    DatasetMetadata
    DatasetMetadata stores essential information about dataset represented by Dataset, for example: minimum rating value, maximum rating value, number of items, number of users, etc.
    DatasetPair
    This contains a pair of dataset such as training dataset and testing dataset.
    DatasetPool
    This class contains a list of dataset pairs.
    DatasetUtil
    This utility class, called dataset utility, provides utility methods processing on Dataset such as loading dataset and saving dataset.
    Datasource
    Data source represented by Datasource class is a special class used to point to a dataset.
    ExternalConfig
    This class specified the configuration including external information stored in outside database different from Hudup framework database.
    ExternalItemInfo
    Items represent many kinds of goods such as books, clothes.
    ExternalRecord
    The class represents an external record stored in other database (different from the framework database).
    ExternalUserInfo
    User has a lot of additional information.
    FetcherMetadata
    This class contains additional information about Fetcher.
    FetcherUtil
    This utility class provides utility methods to process on Fetcher.
    HiddenText
    This class represents a hidden text.
    InterchangeAttributeMap
    This class includes both internal record represented by InternalRecord class and external record represented by ExternalRecord class.
    InternalRecord
    This class represents a single-value record of a unit in framework database.
    Item
    This class represent profile of an item, called item profile, which inherits directly Profile.
    ItemPaddingMatrix
    The first row is list of user id (s).
    ItemRating
    This class extending the RatingVector class represents a item rating vector that contains all ratings of many users on the same item and so the internal variable RatingVector.id is item identification (item ID).
    KBasePointer
    There are two typical Dataset such as Snapshot and Scanner.
    Keys
    This class represents a list of key attributes.
    MemFetcher<E>
    This class implements a fetcher Fetcher whose data elements are stored in memory.
    MemProfiles
    This class represents a collection of many profiles.
    MetaFetcher<U,V>  
    Nominal
    This class represent nominal data type called nominal in brief.
    NominalList
    This class represent a list of nominal (s), called nominal list, in brief.
    ObjectPair<T>
    This class is the pair of key and value.
    ObjectVector<E extends java.io.Serializable>
    This class represents a vector of objects.
    PaddingMatrix
    This class represents a matrix where the first row is list of item or user identifiers.
    Pair
    This class represents a pair of key and value.
    ParamSql
    This class represents a SQL statement having parameters, called parametric SQL.
    Pointer
    This is abstract class of pointer.
    Profile
    Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values.
    PropList
    This utility class stores dictionary of entries.
    ProviderAssocAbstract
    This abstract class implements partially the ProviderAssoc interface.
    Rating
    This class represents a rating that a user gives on an item.
    RatingMatrix
    This class represents a rating matrix contains a set of rows and a set of columns in table form.
    RatingMatrixMetadata
    This class represents meta-data of rating matrix for storing additional information of rating matrix.
    RatingMulti
    This class is firstly similar to Rating contains ratings of one user giving on many items or ratings of one item receiving from many users.
    RatingTriple
    This class contains the rating that a user gives on an item, including three following parts: The rating represented by Rating class. User identification (user ID). Item identification (item ID).
    RatingVector
    This class represents a vector (an array) of ratings.
    Scanner
    This is abstract class of scanner.
    ServerPointer
    There are two typical Dataset such as Snapshot and Scanner.
    Snapshot
    This is abstract class of snapshot.
    SysConfig
    Note, a configuration represented by DataConfig class stores configuration properties.
    Unit
    Objects in framework such as profile, item profile, user profile, rating matrix, interchanged attribute map are stored in archives (files) of entire framework.
    UnitList
    This class represents a list of many units.
    User
    This class represent profile of an item, called item profile, which inherits directly Profile.
    UserPaddingMatrix
    This class represents a matrix where the first row is list of item id (s).
    UserRating
    This class extending the RatingVector class represents a user rating vector that contains all ratings of the same user on many items and so the internal variable RatingVector.id is user identification (user ID).
    Wrapper
    This is the wrapper of any object.
